This paper focuses on modeling the interplay between different modes of content (text, images, videos, and audio) in social media and how they attract user attention and engagement. It also takes into account context factors such as timing effects, community preferences, and social factors. This work involves natural language processing (NLP), computer vision (CV), and information retrieval (IR) techniques, which are all subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
